# BLoC Layer Rules

## Bloc, never Cubit
- ❌ NEVER extend `Cubit` — always use `Bloc<Event, State>`
- Every BLoC must have a typed sealed `Event` class and a `State` class

## Race conditions — bloc_concurrency
Use `bloc_concurrency` transformers for all async event handlers:

```dart
import 'package:bloc_concurrency/bloc_concurrency.dart';

// ✅ GOOD — user_config ThemeBloc
ThemeBloc(...) : super(const ThemeState()) {
  on<ThemeStarted>(_onStarted, transformer: droppable());       // ignore taps while loading
  on<ThemeModeChanged>(_onModeChanged, transformer: sequential()); // queue saves
  on<ThemeSystemRefreshed>(_onSystemRefreshed, transformer: restartable()); // only latest
}

// ❌ BAD — no transformer; concurrent taps can corrupt state
on<ThemeModeChanged>(_onModeChanged);
```

## Imports
- ❌ NO imports from any `data/` layer — BLoC only sees domain (usecases, entities, failures)
- ❌ NO `Analytics.track(...)` calls — analytics belong exclusively in UseCases
- ✅ `flutter_bloc`, `bloc_concurrency`, `injectable`, `freezed_annotation`, own feature's `domain/`, `core/bloc/`

## Event structure — Freezed sealed class

Events MUST use `@freezed sealed class` with named factory constructors, exactly like states.
Each factory variant generates a concrete class used in `on<Variant>(...)` handlers.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — user_config: theme_event.dart (part of theme_bloc.dart)
@freezed
sealed class ThemeEvent with _$ThemeEvent {
  const factory ThemeEvent.started(AppThemeMode systemThemeMode) = ThemeStarted;
  const factory ThemeEvent.modeChanged(AppThemeMode mode) = ThemeModeChanged;
  const factory ThemeEvent.systemRefreshed(AppThemeMode systemThemeMode) = ThemeSystemRefreshed;
}

// ✅ GOOD — user_config: locale_event.dart (part of locale_bloc.dart)
@freezed
sealed class LocaleEvent with _$LocaleEvent {
  const factory LocaleEvent.started({required String deviceLanguageCode}) = LocaleStarted;
  const factory LocaleEvent.changed(String languageCode) = LocaleChanged;
}

// ❌ BAD — plain abstract class, no Freezed
abstract class ThemeEvent {}
class ThemeStarted extends ThemeEvent {
  final AppThemeMode systemThemeMode;
  ThemeStarted(this.systemThemeMode);
}

// ❌ BAD — sealed without Freezed, manual boilerplate
sealed class ThemeEvent {
  const ThemeEvent();
}
class ThemeStarted extends ThemeEvent {
  const ThemeStarted(this.systemThemeMode);
  final AppThemeMode systemThemeMode;
}
```

Named constructor convention: `EventClass.verbNoun(...)` = `ConcreteVariantClass`
- `ThemeEvent.started(...)` → `ThemeStarted`
- `ThemeEvent.modeChanged(...)` → `ThemeModeChanged`
- `LocaleEvent.changed(...)` → `LocaleChanged`

## State structure
Use `StateStatus` for async status and `Failure?` (typed field) for errors. Never use `String? errorMessage`.

```dart
// ❌ BAD — current violation in user_config
@freezed
sealed class ThemeState with _$ThemeState {
  const factory ThemeState({
    @Default(StateStatus.initial) StateStatus status,
    String? errorMessage,    // ❌ raw string, loses type info
  }) = _ThemeState;
}

// ✅ GOOD
@freezed
sealed class ThemeState with _$ThemeState {
  const factory ThemeState({
    AppThemeMode? themeMode,
    AppThemeMode? systemThemeMode,
    AppThemeMode? appliedThemeMode,
    @Default(StateStatus.initial) StateStatus status,
    Failure? failure,        // ✅ typed Failure keeps FailureType for UI routing
  }) = _ThemeState;
}
```

For features with input fields, use `FieldState<T>` — never `TextEditingController`:

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — hypothetical user_config profile edit state
@freezed
sealed class UserConfigEditState with _$UserConfigEditState {
  const factory UserConfigEditState({
    @Default(StateStatus.initial) StateStatus status,
    Failure? failure,
    @Default(FieldState(value: '')) FieldState<String> displayName,
    @Default(FieldState(value: '')) FieldState<String> email,
  }) = _UserConfigEditState;
}
```

## inlineError → FieldState mapping
If `failure.type == FailureType.inlineError`, map to the specific `FieldState` — never surface as top-level `failure`:

```dart
result.fold(
  (failure) {
    if (failure.type == FailureType.inlineError) {
      // Map to the specific field — keep out of top-level failure
      emit(state.copyWith(
        displayName: state.displayName.copyWith(
          status: FieldStatus.invalid,
          error: failure.message,
        ),
      ));
    } else {
      emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.error, failure: failure));
    }
  },
  (_) => emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.success, failure: null)),
);
```

